SUMMARY:Repair Deli
DESCRIPTION:Do you have any items around the house that need mending or repairing? Bring them to the Repair Deli! \nMontclair Area Solidarity Network is hosting a Repair Deli at the HUUB on Saturday\, March 21st\, 2026 from 10am to 3pm. Volunteers will be available to mend clothes\, fix up bikes\, sharpen knives\, and repair lamps\, wooden items\, small electronics\, and more. Examples of repairs include patching up holes in fabrics\, adjusting bike brakes\, or replacing a clasp on a bracelet. \nTransit options:\n– Public transit encouraged. The Orange train station is 0.3 miles away. Buses 21\, 41\, 71\, and 92 are also options.\n– If you are driving: Limited street parking is available. Accessible parking available upon request—please mention it in your RSVP. \nFree event. Please limit to 2 items per person. Last entry is at 2:30pm. \nRSVP is recommended. Register at https://tinyurl.com/RepairDeli. \nLet’s take care of our items and keep them out of landfills! \nFeel free to contact Montclair Area Solidarity Network (MASN) for more information.\nWebsite: www.montclairsolidarity.org\nEmail: montclairsolidarity@gmail.com\nInstagram: @montclairsolidarity \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/repair-deli/
LOCATION:The HUUB\, 35 Cleveland St\, Orange\, 07050\, United States
