SUMMARY:Gardening for Hummingbirds
DESCRIPTION:Duncan earned his doctorate in Ornamental Horticulture at Cornell University. His career has taken him on a journey through horticulture: he taught college for 24 years\, worked as the Education Manager at Mt. Cuba Center\, managed a 20-acre estate in Greenwich\, CT\, designed landscapes for both private and public clients\, and has contributed to many horticultural publications. He continues to design landscapes\, promote ecologically focused gardening practices\, and lecture on his passion\, native plants.  Duncan will help us explore the life cycle of the ruby-throated hummingbird\, and show us how to make our gardens a haven for these tiny flying jewels\, including a great selection of native plants that provide food sources and nesting sites from spring to fall. \nThe Garden Club of Montclair holds programs throughout the year that are open to the community.  We invite renown horticultural experts to speak to club members on a variety of topics\, and we welcome non-members to join us.  There is no fee; a $5 -$10 donation per person is very much appreciated. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
